divs: Sighting Details Went outside around 10:25pm to smoke a cigarete I was Standing on back deck which faces south, object appeared in night sky heading in a north west direction. Six iridescent white round lights on each side in a large V shape was not low in sky. No sound, movement was very smooth almost like gliding. Sky was overcast, not alot of moonlight. Object did not put off light, formation never changed, direction never changed it did not accend or decend in the sky. Lost sight of object when it passed over neighbors roof line and my view was blocked . I want to know what this was. I have no explaination of what this could have been, I cannot explain it away as being an airplane, helicopter, wheather balloon or flairs. I want to know if anyone else saw this or reported it to the airport, police ect. I have lived in this area my entire life and never seen anything like this.
